# Formatting Rules

When writing JSX/TSX code, follow these formatting rules:

1. **Children on new lines**: All child elements/components should be on their own line, not inline with the opening tag
2. **Blank lines between siblings**: Add a blank line between sibling elements/components that share the same parent

## Examples

### Correct Formatting:
```tsx
<div className={s.container}>
  <span className={s.label}>LABEL:</span>

  <div className={s.content}>
    <Text>First child</Text>

    <Text>Second child</Text>

    <ul>
      <li>Item 1</li>

      <li>Item 2</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>
```

### Incorrect Formatting:
```tsx
// ❌ Children inline
<div className={s.container}><span>Label</span><div>Content</div></div>

// ❌ No blank lines between siblings
<div>
  <span>First</span>
  <span>Second</span>
</div>
```

Always format code following these rules when editing or creating JSX/TSX files.
